snippet.textDisplay:
To Zach and everyone else it might concern: You do not NEED to wash your face! Washing it excessively could even upset the balance of the skin and just like your hair, you really should only do it when necessary. If you have nice skin (like Zachs), it takes really good care of itself and you only risk unbalancing it. And do NOT use cheap creams or moisturizers either, same issue, and you may even become dependent on them because you upset the balance! Don't let excessive skin care create problems for you if you don't already have them!
Exceptions:
1. If you pick on your face or touch your face a lot. (especially now, but you should rather try to stop touching it than washing it more often if possible)
2. If it gets dirty. This includes eyegunk or sleepdrool or if you tend to sleep with your face in the pillow, and obviously if you use makeup.
3. If you already have skin issues.
Other than that, avoid washing your face. If you have to, avoid (almost all kinds) of soap, and avoid too hot water. All those things will dry out your skin.
